column6: notes
Netflix brand uses distinctive red (#E50914) with black (#221F1F) and white; the color palette is widely recognized and used across its logo and interface.
Spotify's primary brand color is Spotify Green (#1DB954). Black (#191414) and white are used for contrast and backgrounds.
YouTube's palette consists of YouTube Red (#FF0000), an almost black shade (#282828) and white. These colors are used consistently across the brand.
Hulu's guidelines specify using Hulu Green (#1CE783) wherever possible. If placed on a green background, the logo may be black (#040405). A secondary green (#29A869) is used sparingly.
Disney+ updated its branding in 2024, shifting from a gradient to a unified deep teal/blue palette. The logo commonly uses a dark blue (#113CCF) and teal (#0A5C73) with white lettering.
Prime Video uses a bright blue (#1399FF) as its primary color alongside black and white. These values are approximations based on the Amazon Prime Blue palette.
Paramount+ uses Paramount blue (#0060A3) in its logos. White lettering or a white background is often paired with this blue.
Max (formerly HBO Max) uses a deep indigo or dark purple (#1A237E) and monochrome palette in its recent rebrand.
Notion’s brand is intentionally monochrome, primarily black on white, reflecting a minimalist design philosophy.
Dropbox uses a strong blue (#0061FF) for its logo with white or black as supporting colors.
Microsoft 365 draws on Microsoft’s four-color palette: orange (#F25022), green (#7FBA00), blue (#00A4EF) and yellow (#FFB900).
Google One follows Google’s four standard colors: blue (#4285F4), red (#EA4335), yellow (#FBBC05), and green (#34A853).
Evernote’s primary color is a vibrant green (#2DCE89); it is paired with black or white backgrounds.
Patreon uses a coral orange (#F96854) and deep navy (#05192D) as its primary brand colors.
PlayStation branding uses a deep blue (#003087) along with black and white for contrast.
The Xbox brand uses a bold green (#107C10) with white and black for its Game Pass logos.
Amazon Music Unlimited generally uses a bright azure blue (#00BBFF) along with black and white.
Tencent Video uses a bright blue (#00C6FF) as its primary color; white and black provide contrast.
iQIYI’s logo uses a vivid green (#00DC5A) wordmark; black or white may be used as background.
Youku’s logo pairs a vibrant blue (#00A0E9) with red (#FF0000). White is used for contrast.
Bilibili’s palette mixes blue (#00A1E9) and pink (#FB7299), reflecting the platform’s playful aesthetic. These values are widely used although formal guidelines are not public.
WeChat’s primary color is green (#09BB07); logos may appear on black or white backgrounds.
Apple Music uses a gradient pink/red palette (e.g., #FF4E6B and #FF0436). Official guidelines focus on using Apple-provided artwork; color values are approximate.
Apple TV+ follows Apple’s monochrome signature: black and white, without additional colors.
Apple Arcade uses a vivid red (#FF453A) in its logo, with white as contrast. Values are approximate.
iCloud+ is often represented with a sky-blue cloud icon (#3693F3) on a white background; colors are approximate.
Audible’s logo features a warm orange (#F8991C) combined with black and white.
Kindle Unlimited aligns with Amazon’s orange (#FF9900) paired with black and white.
Adobe Creative Cloud uses a gradient of red (#FF0000), magenta (#EC008C) and orange (#F79E1B) in its swirl logo.
Crunchyroll’s official color is orange (#F47521). The logo may appear in white on colored backgrounds.
Tidal’s branding is largely monochromatic (black and white) accented by a cyan-blue (#00B4D8) in some contexts.
Deezer’s logo uses a multi-color equalizer motif with red (#FA0B0B), yellow (#FEEB0B), green (#33FF62), blue (#00A8E0) and purple (#C402E4).
LinkedIn uses a distinctive blue (#0077B5) together with black and white for its premium services.
NordVPN’s brand features a cool blue (#007FFF) with white and black to convey trust and security.
ExpressVPN’s logo uses a bold red (#DA3940) with white.
Canva’s brand palette includes teal (#00C4CC), coral (#FF6F61) and purple (#8338EC), reflecting its creative platform.
Figma’s logo uses four circles in different colors: orange (#F24E1E), purple (#A259FF), green (#0ACF83), and coral (#FF7262).
ChatGPT’s branding uses a distinctive green (#10A37F) along with black and white.
Midjourney uses a purple hue (#5A4C8F) and often pairs it with black or white.
Coursera’s palette centers on a deep blue (#0056D2) with white.
Chegg uses a bright orange (#FFB800) for its identity paired with white.
Slack’s hashtag logo contains four colors: purple (#611F69), blue (#36C5F0), green (#2EB67D), and pink (#E01E5A).
GitHub’s branding uses black (#181717) with white; the green (#6CC644) appears in Octocat imagery.
QQ’s palette includes yellow (#F9AE08), red (#EA1C26), black and white. These values come from QQ brand guidelines.
Kugou’s logo uses a vivid blue (#0179F1) paired with white.
Baidu’s corporate palette includes blue (#2932E1) and red (#DE0F17). These colors extend to Baidu Wenku.
WPS Office uses a bright orange-red (#E94D2B) for its logo.
Zhihu’s primary color is blue (#0084FF). It is paired with black and white in the brand’s visual identity.
Udemy’s branding often uses a gradient from red (#EC5252) to purple (#A435F0) combined with white.
Douyin (TikTok in mainland China) uses neon cyan (#00F8FF) and pink (#FF0050) against black backgrounds; white may be used for text.
